    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: HORTON ON/OFF - TROUBLESHOOTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl1200405">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
            <title>AIR SUPPLY</title>
            <para>There should be a steady supply of clean air at 90-120 psi to the fan solenoid.</para>
            <para>Verify that there are no leaks in the piping or fan clutch assembly. (Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s12004r_HL1200401.xml" xrefid="hl1200401">SYSTEM CHECKS</hotlnk>, and
                <hotlnk document="s12004r_HL1200402.xml" xrefid="hl1200402">PREVENTIVE MAINTENANCE</hotlnk>.)
            </para>
            <table id="hl1200406">
                <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2.09in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.89in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.99in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>CONDITION</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>PROBABLE CAUSE</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>REMEDY</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>Fan won't cycle when the air conditioning test is performed.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The outside air temperature is too low, there is a low refrigerant charge or the
                                    refrigerant pressure switch is faulty.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the A/C system.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the pressure switch if required.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>Overtemp warning activates before the fan engages.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Defective overtemp warning switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the overtemp warning switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>The engine appears to overheat. The fan won't engage when the engine cooland temp
                                    gauge is above 195-205&#176;F (91-96&#176;C) or overtemp warning activates before
                                    the fan engages.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The air solenoid valve may be plumbed incorrectly.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the solenoid plumbing. Replumb the valve.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The overtemp warning switch is faulty (the warning light activates prematurely).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the overtemp warning switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The overtemp warning switch is too far away from the fan temp switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Move the overtemp warning switch as close to the fan temp switch as possible.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Temp gauge is faulty (reads high).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the temp sensor.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The fan temp switch is faulty.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace fan temp switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>The fan engages at low engine temperatures while the vehicle is moving.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The normal condition in extremely hot weather or at low vehicle speeds in warm
                                    weather with the A/C on.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>A normal condition.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Faulty temp gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the temp sender or gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The A/C system is overcharged or the condenser is covered with debris.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the A/C system.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The refrigerant pressure switch may be faulty.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the pressure switch if necessary.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The fan temperature switch is faulty if the fan engages at low engine temperature
                                    and the A/C is off.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the fan temp switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>The fan won't run under any condition.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The air line may be leaking.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the air lines and repair if necessary.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The wiring may be faulty and/or the circuit breaker tripped.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the wiring and circuit breakers.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The air solenoid may be faulty. Test the air solenoid valve by shorting across the
                                    terminals of the temp switch to energize the air solenoid valve and activate the fan
                                    drive.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>If the solenoid does not activate, replace the solenoid.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>The fan runs continually when the air conditioning is off.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The air solenoid valve may be faulty or plumbed incorrectly.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the air solenoid valve plumbing and replace the valve if faulty.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The fan temp switch may be stuck open; with the engine temp below 180&#176;F (82&#176;C)
                                    short across the terminals; if the fan turns off, the switch is faulty.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the fan temp switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The pressure switch may be stuck open. Turn the A/C system off; if the fan
                                    continues to run, short across the pressure switch. If the fan stops, the pressure
                                    switch is defective.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the pressure switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>The fan runs continually when the air conditioning is on.</para>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>This is a normal condition in extremely hot weather. To test, spray water on the
                                    A/C condenser and the fan should disengage briefly and re-engage when the water
                                    evaporates.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>A normal condition in hot weather.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The air conditioning system may be overcharged or the condenser covered with
                                    debris. Turn the A/C system OFF and if the fan stops, the refrigerant pressure
                                    switch is functioning.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Service the A/C system, check the A/C pressure and condenser.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The pressure switch may have drifted out of calibration. Use a pressure gauge to
                                    compare actual fan on and fan off pressures against the specified pressures.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>If out of calibration, replace the pressure switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>Fan operation is erratic.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Loose electrical connection.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the wiring and repair where necessary.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Fan temp or pressure switch may be faulty.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>If other system components check out okay:</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the pressure switch if erratic fan operation associated with the A/C at
                                    idle.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the fan temp switch if the erratic operation occurs primarily when the
                                    engine is hot.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>The fan frequently cycles when the engine is hot.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>The fan should remain engaged long enough to reduce the temperature 7-10&#176;F
                                    from the normal operating temperature. The fan switch is defective if the fan
                                    disengages after only a 3-4&#176;F reduction.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Replace the fan temp switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>The fan turns on whenever the ignition is on and turns off when the engine is
                                    hot.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Air solenoid valve plumbed backwards.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the solenoid installation instructions; plumb correctly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>If the circuit breaker trips whenever the ignition is turned on, the problem is
                                    most likely a fault in the wiring.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Check the wiring and repair where necessary.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>If the circuit breaker trips only when the fan engages, the fault is probably with
                                    the solenoid valve.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Use an ohmmeter to check for a shorted solenoid coil. The coil resistance should
                                    be greater than 14 ohms. If shorted, replace the air solenoid valve.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>The fan frequently cycles when parked with the A/C on.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>This is a normal condition caused by the refrigerant pressure rising to 300 psi
                                    with no air flow through the condenser and then dropping below 250 psi when the fan
                                    turns on.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcproc>
